{
  "doc_id": "18752",
  "text": "The most common strategies for effective perioperative pain management in major abdominal surgery are patient-controlled intravenous opioid analgesia (IV-PCA) and epidural analgesia (EDA) [CITATION_1] . A retrospective study of perioperative pain management strategies in pancreatic surgery published in 2008 [CITATION_2] found that EDA with additional intravenous analgesia was associated with a lower occurrence of postoperative gastrointestinal and infectious complications than EDA alone. The aim of the trial described here is to verify this association in a multicenter RCT.",
